============================================================
4.2 DATA STRUCTURES
============================================================

SnakeSegment:

data SnakeSegment {
    x: int => 0;
    y: int => 0;
    color: string => "#00ff00";
    size: int => 20;
}

Represents one segment of the snake.

Each segment has:
- x, y position on grid
- color (green)
- size (square size)

------------------------------------------------------------

Food:

data Food {
    x: int => 0;
    y: int => 0;
    color: string => "#ff0000";
    size: int => 20;
}

Represents food in the game.

------------------------------------------------------------

GameState:

data GameState {
    snake: SnakeSegment[] => [];
    food: Food => Food();
    direction_x: int => 1;
    direction_y: int => 0;
    segment_size: int => 20;
    game_width: int => 800;
    game_height: int => 600;
    score: int => 0;
    game_over: bool => false;
    last_tick: int => 1;
}

This is the full game state:
- snake body
- food position
- movement direction
- score
- timing

