============================================================
4.4 INITIALIZATION
============================================================

FUNCTION:

fn init_game_state() -> GameState

EXPLANATION:

Creates initial game state:

- snake starts in center
- food is randomly placed
- direction = right
- score = 0

Key idea:
This function builds the first "snapshot" of the game world.

------------------------------------------------------------


============================================================
4.5 GAME UPDATE LOGIC
============================================================

FUNCTION:

fn update_game_state(mut state: GameState) -> GameState

EXPLANATION:

This is the core game engine logic.

STEP 1 — Move snake head:
- calculates new position

STEP 2 — Screen wrapping:
- if snake goes out of bounds → appears on opposite side

STEP 3 — Create new snake:
- always rebuilds snake state

STEP 4 — Collision with food:
- increase score
- move food
- grow snake

STEP 5 — Movement without food:
- remove tail segment
- simulate movement

Key idea:
Each frame creates a new version of GameState.

------------------------------------------------------------


