============================================================
4.7 MAIN LOOP
============================================================

CODE:

@entry
fn main() {
    mut game: GameState => init_game_state();

    mut win => ui.create(
        title => "Vice Snake",
        size => [game.game_width, game.game_height],
        color => "#202020"
    );

    while (win : is_open) {

        INPUT:
        - arrow keys change direction
        - prevents reversing instantly

        UPDATE:
        - runs every 150ms
        - calls update_game_state

        RENDER:
        - draws snake and food

    }
}

EXPLANATION:

This is a classic GAME LOOP:

1. Read input
2. Update world state
3. Render frame
4. Repeat

This pattern is used in almost all games.

